text: Kieran John Modra (27 March 1972 â€“ 13 November 2019) was an Australian Paralympic swimmer and tandem cyclist. He won five gold and five bronze medals at eight Paralympic Games from 1988 to 2016, along with two silver medals at the 2014 Glasgow Commonwealth Games. Modra died after his bike crashed with a car on the Sturt Highway in Kingsford on 13 November 2019. ==References== Category:1972 births Category:2019 deaths Category:Road accident deaths Category:Australian swimmers Category:Sportspeople from South Australia Category:Australian cyclists
